The paper deals with knowledge representation in medical expert systems, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of rough set theory and lattice structure for knowledge representation suggests a focus on machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) techniques. The problem of redundancy and inconsistency in knowledge also suggests a possible connection to databases (cs.DB). The case study on low back pain management suggests a focus on healthcare (cs.HC) applications. Finally, the paper's emphasis on computational efficiency suggests a possible connection to cybernetics (cs.CY).
